<br>
Arch skills<br>
-  Spell Casting Mastery - One of the best.  With the high cost of the new mezz spells, any mana saving is a blessing.  Good to get if your specialization is conjuration.  Really makes a difference.<br>
-  Spell Casting Reinforcement - Neat but not critical.  Since you usually buff during down times this will not be a life saver.  Good to get eventually.<br>
-  Spell Casting Fury - A toy and nothing more.  Get when you have nothing else to spend on.<br>
- Channeling Focus - Very important.  Channeling a mezz or a slow through getting beat on is critical.<br>
- Spell Casting Subtelty - If you raid a lot, this will save you from death tashing.  In groups, it's less important if you can manage your agro well.<br>
- Spell Casting Expertise - utter crap<br>
- Spell Casting Deftness - not as bad as expertise I guess, but I would rather buy innate metabolism<br>
- Natural Durability - Life Saver.  Extra HP = Good.<br>
- Combat Stability / Agility - Neat but not crucial<br>
- Mental Clarity - Very nice but only the first level is really worth the points.  However, it is a prerequizite to Gather Mana which is a life saver.<br>
<br>
My recommendation, ask yourself, &quot;what gets me in trouble?&quot;  Is it running out of mana?  or running out of HP?  If mana is your issue, go with SCM / MC / Gather Mana.  If HP are your problem go with Channeling Focus, Subtelty and Natural Durability.  Each of these is different so make sure you analyze your play style and see what will help you the most.  You may also want to think about Eldritch Rune.<br>
<br>
For example, when I was buying these skillls, I noticed I never really ran out of mana, but I was having serious issues with getting beat on.  I tend to tash early, I tash a lot of high level mobs on FE raids which like to beat on me and I like tanking mobs for my pet while I solo.  So I went with Channeling Focus and Subtelty.  If I was making the same decision these days I would probably go with SCM and MC / Gather mana because the new mezzes cost so much mana.  It all depends on your play style though.<br>
<br>
One more thing, it's more cost effective to buy a few first levels in multiple skills than it to buy all three levels in one.  The 12 points you spend to get 3 levels of one skill could have been better spent getting multiple lower levels of other skills.  The only exception would be prerequisite skills like Mental Clarity which you need to get in order to buy other skills.<br>
<br>
Feel free to send me a tell if you want to hear more or just post it here. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><br>
